Privacy Policy - Housy Inspect
Effective Date: January 26, 2026

Last Updated: January 26, 2026

About Housy Inspect
Housy Inspect is a professional home inspection management platform that connects service providers (inspectors, inspection companies) with customers requiring home inspection services. Our platform enables inspection businesses and independent professionals to manage their operations efficiently.

Who Can Use This App
Service Providers: Professional home inspection companies, independent inspectors, and certified professionals who partner with our platform
Account Access: Accounts are created after verification of professional credentials and business registration
Multi-Tenant Platform: Multiple businesses and service providers use our platform to serve their customers
Information We Collect
1. Account Information
Business name and registration details
Professional certifications and licenses
Contact information (name, email, phone number)
Login credentials
2. Location Data
When In Use Only: Location is collected only when the app is actively open
Used for attendance tracking during work sessions
Used for navigation to inspection sites
Background Location: We do NOT collect location when the app is closed or in background
3. Inspection Data
Property inspection photos, videos, and voice notes
Inspection reports and documentation
Customer property information (address, inspection details)
Work assignment and scheduling data
4. Device Information
Device type and operating system
App version and performance data
Crash reports for technical support
How We Use Your Information
For Service Providers:
Account verification and onboarding
Work assignment and task management
Attendance tracking during active work sessions
Performance monitoring and quality assurance
Payment processing and invoicing
Technical support and app improvements
For Customers:
Inspection scheduling and coordination
Report generation and delivery
Quality assurance and customer service
Data Sharing and Disclosure
We respect your privacy and limit data sharing to:

We Share With:
Customers: Inspection reports and service-related information
Your Organization: If you work for an inspection company, your employer may access work-related data
Service Providers: Third-party services for app functionality (cloud hosting, analytics)
Legal Compliance: When required by law or to protect rights and safety
We Do NOT:
Sell your personal information to third parties
Share data for marketing purposes without consent
Use your data beyond stated purposes
Location Services
When In Use Permission:
Our app requests "When In Use" location permission for:

Attendance check-in/check-out during work sessions
Navigation to inspection sites
Service delivery verification
Important:
Location tracking stops when you close the app
Location is not collected in background or when app is minimized
You can disable location in device settings (may limit app functionality)
Data Security
We implement industry-standard security measures:

Encryption: All data is encrypted in transit and at rest
Secure Servers: Data stored on secure cloud infrastructure
Access Controls: Restricted access to authorized personnel only
Regular Audits: Security assessments and updates
Data Retention
Active Accounts: Data retained while your account is active
Inactive Accounts: Data may be retained for legal/compliance requirements
Deletion Requests: You can request account deletion (subject to legal obligations)
Inspection Records: Retained as per regulatory requirements and business needs
Your Rights
You have the right to:

Access: Request a copy of your personal data
Correction: Update or correct inaccurate information
Deletion: Request deletion of your data (subject to legal requirements)
Portability: Receive your data in a portable format
Withdraw Consent: Opt-out of non-essential data processing
Account Access and Termination
Partner Onboarding: Contact our business team for verification and account creation
Account Deactivation: Accounts are deactivated when partnership ends or upon request
Data After Termination: Certain data retained for legal compliance
Third-Party Services
We may use third-party services for:

Cloud storage and hosting
Analytics and performance monitoring
Payment processing
Communication services (email, SMS, push notifications)
These providers are contractually bound to protect your data.

Children's Privacy
Our services are not intended for children under 18. We do not knowingly collect data from children. This is a professional business application.

Changes to Privacy Policy
We may update this policy periodically. Changes will be:

Posted in the app and on our website
Notified via email for significant changes
Effective date updated at the top
Compliance
This privacy policy complies with:

Information Technology Act, 2000 (India)
Apple App Store Guidelines
Google Play Store Policies
General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) where applicable
